      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $A\\subset\\mathbb{N}$ be an additive basis of order $k$ which is minimal, in the sense that if $B\\subset A$ is any infinite set then $A\\backslash B$ is not a basis of order $k$. \n\nMust there exist an infinite $B\\subset A$ such that $A\\backslash B$ is a basis of order $k+1$?"
    }
